                "name": "Steal Fire",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su",
                "text": "As a standard action, a kijimuna can call out to a nonmagical fire within 30 feet equivalent in size to the flames of a burning torch. Doing so causes the flame to become a light similar to that created by a <i>dancing lights</i> spell, under the control of the kijimuna. An attended object can make a DC 13 Reflex saving throw to avoid this effect. Unlike a <i>dancing lights </i>spell, a kijimuna\u2019s steal fire ability can cause a stolen fire to strike a creature, either ringing the target in light as per the spell <i>faerie fire </i>for 5 minutes, or dealing 2d6 points of fire damage (DC 13 Reflex, half ). Both save DCs are Charisma-based. A lantern, candle, torch, or similar item that has its flame stolen cannot be relit by any means for 24 hours."
            }
